-- Vivendi Slumps After La Tribune Report on Ending of Favorable Tax Status
-- B y   D a v i d   W h i t e h o u s e
-- 2010-11-12T08:07:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-12/vivendi-slumps-after-la-tribune-report-on-ending-of-favorable-tax-status.html
Vivendi SA shares fell after La
Tribune reported that the company’s tax status, which allows it
to deduct losses incurred abroad from domestic profit, won’t be
renewed at the end of 2011.  The shares fell as much as 3.2 percent and were down 3
percent at 19.95 euros at 9:06 a.m. in Paris.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Whitehouse at 
 dwhitehouse1@bloomberg.net  